casebody.data:
ZIVI, Respondent, v. EINSTEIN, Appellant. (Common Pleas of New York City and County,

General Term.

May 8, 1893.) Action by Bernard Zivi against Elias Einstein.

Argued before BOOKSTAYER, BISCHOFF, and PRYOR, JJ.

Townsend, Dyett & Einstein, for appellant. Jas. Murphy, for respondent

No opinion. Motion for leave to go to the court of appeals denied. See 21 N. Y. Supp. 583.
